manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Color Assortment From the bright and stylish design to the accent pops of color, you will never have to worry about keeping track of these eye-catchers! Black Blue/Navy Silver Emerald Graphite Grey Rose Samsonite Winfield 3 DLX Tough and light, Winfield 3 DLX is the latest generation of one of Samsonite’s most popular collections. This deluxe iteration has been upgraded with a 4-pocket 2-sided divider panel that cleverly maximizes packing organization without extra bulk or weight. Made from polycarbonate that offers great protection for your belongings, Winfield 3 DLX also features an integrated TSA lock, sturdy spinner wheels, and a comfortable pull handle for an easy and confident travel experience. 20" Spinner | Overall Dimensions: 22.5" x 14.5" x 9.5", Weight: 6.97 lbs. 24" Spinner | Overall Dimensions: 27.0" x 17.25" x 11.375", Weight: 8.9 lbs. 28" Spinner | Overall Dimensions: 30.5" x 20.5" x 13.25", Weight: 10.96 lbs.

Functional and Thoughtful Design Push-Button Handle Deluxe cushioning and soft rubber seals on our new, wider pull handle combine to provide an exceptionally comfortable grip. Integrated, multi-stage aluminum pull handle for extra lightness. Retracting top and side carry-handles remain protected when checking baggage. 360 Spinner Wheels This lightweight line offers heavyweight protection riding on effortless 360 degree Spinner Wheels. All you need to do is push your case along and the wheels do the rest. Whether you are checking into to the flight or your hotel, it is super-easy with spinner wheels. TSA Compatible Combination Lock Side-mounted TSA lock ensure your belongings arrive safely to your destination. With a built in combination lock, the Samsonite cases are good to go no matter where you are. No keys required!

TSA Combination Lock How to Use the TSA Combination Lock Our TSA-approved combination locks are simple and easy to use, no key required! Use a ballpoint pen or other pointed object to press the small button located near the dials. With the button pressed in, set the dials to your desired code, and slide the button with the key hole towards to the dials to set. The code is now ready to use. The key hole is intended only for use by TSA agents, and no keys are included or required to use our TSA combination locks. The factory default code for new luggage is 0-0-0.

About Samsonite Samsonite’s not just in the business of making luggage, we’re in the business of building confidence. Confidence that when you step off the curb, your luggage wheel isn't going to pop off. Confidence that if you put your laptop in the bag in one piece, that’s the way it will come out. Samsonite has set an industry precedence by perfecting and innovating luggage, casual bags, backpacks, travel accessories, and now electronics carriers and laptop bags. Over one hundred years of reliability, durability, style and innovative functionality have made Samsonite’s iconic products, and brand. If you are going to head out the door, do it with peace of mind. Because, life has a way of coming at you fast. Be ready for anywhere.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I should have purchased this a long time ago
reviews.reviewText: I recently invested in the Samsonite 28-Inch Suitcase, and I couldn't be more pleased with my purchase. This suitcase is the epitome of travel convenience and durability. My last similar no-name case lasted about 4 trips so I decided it was time to buy something solid.The size, at 28 inches, strikes the perfect balance between spaciousness and maneuverability. It offers ample room for packing without being overly bulky. The interior organization is top-notch, featuring thoughtful compartments that make packing and unpacking a breeze.Durability is where this suitcase truly shines. The tough exterior material not only withstands the rigors of baggage handling but also looks sleek and sophisticated. The wheels glide effortlessly, and the telescopic handle feels sturdy and reliable. It's amazingly light for it's size and construction.Security is another area where Samsonite excels. The combination lock provides peace of mind, and the zippers feel robust and secure.In terms of aesthetics, the suitcase's design is both timeless and modern. It stands out on the carousel, making it easy to spot amidst a sea of generic luggage.Overall, the Samsonite 28-Inch Suitcase is a stellar investment for anyone who values durability, functionality, and style in their travel gear. I wholeheartedly give it a well-deserved 5-star rating – it's a true travel companion that exceeds expectations.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Luggage that can stand up to airline abuse!
reviews.reviewText: Luggage isn't a frequent purchase and it is a serious investment (for me at least). The Winfield Luggage from Samsonite has been great. I live in Alaska and the luggage doesn't get brittle or crack in the cold. I also travel to hot places (to get away from the cold) and it works well holding up in the heat. The hard sides do not absorb water so if it rains on it, I'm covered. The wheels track nicely on both rough and smooth surfaces and the weight isn't in the luggage, so I can have more "stuff" with me. They look great and hold up to the abuses handed out by the automated airline handling equipment. Small scuffs are not noticeable due to the surface texture. These are going to serve me well for years.

reviews.reviewText: Works well and is roomy. Perfect for my husband’s trip. Wheels work very well-smooth and easy to handle. No issues. Took on international trip and had no complaints.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Functional and light; not meant for road warriors
reviews.reviewText: Bag is super light and looks great. For the occasional traveler, this bag will serve you well and is worth the price. This bag will also serve you well on international flights that severely limit the size and weight of carry-on bags.I've logged 3 cross country trips in one month and find the quality to be decent. The inner lining, straps on each half, and the separator are very well done with good quality construction. The release button on the handle has a full rubber cover; thus, dust will not likely cause issues with the button operation.The issue: single wheel per corner will not likely survive too many trips. The wheels are rather slim and will catch into the expansion joints in concrete as well fall into minor pock marks on other surfaces and cause the bag to suddenly jerk you back. Further, the wheels do not roll smooth on low pile carpets and the casters do not respond quick enough to allow for rapid direction changes.Other things to consider:The zipper pull locks are rather weak and will likely break in time. I do, however, like the lock's ability to keep the zipper handle in place in a tidy manner. I wouldn't trust the lock to keep anyone out...not a problem for me as I rarely check my bags in the belly of the plane.The handle will twist rather easily; thus, you won't always have postive control over the motion of the bag. Then again, this bag is meant to be as light as possible and yet still functional.Happy travels!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to move, tons of space and great quality
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this suitcase for an international trip and am very happy with the purchase. I was very impressed with how easily the suitcase rolled and its light weight. Even with all of my personal belongings, I was still able to maneuver and lift the suitcase for travel. I am also very satisfied with the durability and quality. The hard case stood up through international travel and kept all my belongings save. I liked the different packing options and how it easy it was to organize. Great purchase for a longer trip!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Its Ok... It has good points and not so good points.
reviews.reviewText: So I chose this suitcase after looking at 3 others. I needed to replace my old Samsonite that literally fell apart. Did this one measure up to the old one? I'm not so sure. I'm not so sure I chose the best one either, but it's too late to return, so I'm making due with it.Pros: Color is gorgeous and it stands out. It does pull nicely and maneuvers well. The wheels are strong (My old bag's wheels were not durable). It fits "enough" stuff I guess. I tend to overpack and I feel like I don't get quite as much stuff in here as I would like.Cons: Doesn't feel that durable, as it has a 'softer' plastic like side that I feel will cave in. I wish one of the sides had a zipper closure, its just a flap that flaps back and forth that is used to hold smaller garments or socks/underwear. The "elastic" strap that holds each side of clothes in is VERY loose - it may as well not even be there as it holds nothing. Which leads me to the MAIN thing that drives me crazy about this bag: When I do pack everything in and use the "elastic" strap, When I close the bag - SO MANY ITEMS just fall out as I'm struggling to shove everything back in. Its AWFUL. My old bag had a tighter strap and also a side with a zipper closure. Anyways, since I'm stuck with this bag - I literally bought a bassinet crib sheets and I'm using these sheets as a cover to cover the clothes and items on each side so when I close the bag - nothing randomly falls out. It seems to work, but annoying I have to do this.
I've only taken them on one trip, but so far they seem very durable and well-made. The wheels spin freely and easily and the body of the suitcase is very lightweight.
Me encantaron, se ven finas y las compré en muy buen precio de oferta

I really love the pink colour of this luggage, but that's not all!! I love that it has a divider for one side. The dividers has pockets too! I'm able to organize everything and keep it relatively compact. The extending handle doesn't feel as sturdy as I imagined but seems ok. I will have to give it another review after I use it for travel. I like that it has built in locks and is expandable. The wheels swivel nicely but not as well as my Outbound carry on. All in all I love this new carry on luggage from Samsonite. So sleek and well thought out. Definitely recommend!
